y are needed for any Endure Breath spells that might be given to you!  To end my comments-in total, of buying potions, and donating for TPs/SoWs/Invs/Inv vs Undeads, etc., this Staff cost me a grand total of not more than 100pp.  That comes to an astounding price of 10pp per Int.  Not bad, considering my little level 11 lost only one life during the entirety of the quest.  Only takes a few hours, too, if you are lucky.  Good luck-only thing I would change, would be to have done the quest as soon as I dinged 4 and got Gate.  Being an Erudite, had I known earlier, I would have gotten the two Rods from Erud's Xing and SQey at level 1!  Please post, anyone who has completed the quest at a lower level than 11-curious to know if I hold the record, if even for a little while. hehehe!  See you guys at Crow's!<br>
     Haile Selassie, 12th level Wizard of the Eruditian Council <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24>Staff of the Wheel - Ice Comet</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.3.5<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  